Copyright: Permission given to someone to copy something that they did/legal rights of copying

Copyleft: People can freely distribte copies and modified versions of work you did/ you can use their work but not take credit for it

Fair Use: Can take things and modify them for educational use

Free Speech: The ability to freely express what you believe or feel

Free Software: Can run the program as you wish

Freeware: Software that is available for use

Public Domain: Being available or belongs to public is not subject to copyright

File sharing: Ability to transmit files from one computer to another over networks or the interwebz

Piracy: Using someone else's work without permission

Plagerism: Taking credit for something that you didn't do
